# TypeScript

Strict typing always enabled. Never use `any`, `@ts-ignore`, or `@ts-nocheck`.

## Prefer

- `interface` for object contracts exported across modules
- `type` for unions, intersections, mapped types
- `readonly` on immutable fields
- `const` over `let`
- Type inference when obvious from assignment
- `unknown` + narrowing over `any`

## Avoid

- Non-null assertion (`!`) unless unavoidable with comment why
- Enums when string union + `as const` suffices (Prisma enums are OK)

## This project

- CommonJS modules (`"type": "commonjs"`)
- Express types from `@types/express`
- Extend Express `Request` via `src/shared/types/express.d.ts` for `req.user`

```typescript
// ✅
const payload = verifyAccessToken(token);

// ❌
const payload = verifyAccessToken(token) as any;
```
